body:
Hi, we also found another issue about the 'comb.replicate' operator. It seems that the testing code about it exists in CIRCT, but it's causing errors here.

full error message:
```
STDERR:
home/dhp/work/chisel-prove/examples/src/main/scala/examples/circtErr1.scala:42:18: error: 'comb.replicate' op is an unsupported operation
home/dhp/work/chisel-prove/examples/src/main/scala/examples/circtErr1.scala:42:18: note: see current operation: %3 = "comb.replicate"(%2) : (i1) -> i4
```

how to reproduce:

In chisel, write the following code and emit btor2:
```scala
class GCDe1 extends Module {
    val io = IO(new Bundle {
      val value1    = Input(UInt(16.W))
      val outputGCD = Output(UInt(20.W))
    })

    io.outputGCD := SignExt(io.value1, 200)
    AssertProperty(io.outputGCD === 0.U)

  }

  object SignExt {
    def apply(a: UInt, len: Int): UInt = {
      val aLen    = a.getWidth
      val signBit = a(aLen - 1)
      if (aLen >= len) a(len - 1, 0) else Cat(Fill(len - aLen, signBit), a)
      //   a
    }
  }
```

below is the HW dialect:
```
